            <p>
             The digit in the tens of million place value is <m>1</m>. Therefore, we retain digit <m>2</m> in the hundreds of millions place value and replace the remaining digits by zero.
            </p>
            <p>
              <m>219\, 486\, 272</m> rounded off to the nearest hundred million is <m>200\,000\,000</m>.
            </p>
      </solution>

